00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:57,495 --> 00:01:01,124
THE WONDERFOOLS

2
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:05,086
Excuse me? Nam Sun-gyu?

3
00:01:05,587 --> 00:01:08,298
You say he's working with
the Church of Eternal Salvation

4
00:01:08,381 --> 00:01:09,799
to do what?

5
00:01:10,592 --> 00:01:12,802
Abduct and confine.

6
00:01:25,607 --> 00:01:27,358
<i>Illegal human experiments.</i>

7
00:01:33,448 --> 00:01:34,532
What's going on?

8
00:01:37,202 --> 00:01:39,954
Goodness, ma'am,
why are you bringing up the past?

9
00:01:40,038 --> 00:01:42,165
That happened over 20 years ago.

10
00:01:42,248 --> 00:01:44,584
I'm telling you that
what happened 20 years ago

11
00:01:45,084 --> 00:01:47,670
is happening there again right now!

12
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:56,721
We can just kill them all, right?

13
00:01:56,804 --> 00:01:58,932
Number 3972 is mine.

14
00:01:59,432 --> 00:02:00,600
Hands off.

15
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:47,480
Mr. Oddball, what's wrong with you?

16
00:02:48,231 --> 00:02:50,900
You said you were rechargeable.
Are you out of juice?

17
00:02:51,484 --> 00:02:52,527
Master!

18
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:53,569
Are you okay?

19
00:02:54,153 --> 00:02:57,198
This is not the time
for you to be spacing out.

20
00:02:57,282 --> 00:02:58,574
Come on, Mr. Oddball.

21
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,576
Snap out of it!

22
00:03:05,790 --> 00:03:06,624
Boom boom pow?

23
00:03:23,057 --> 00:03:23,891
Barley.

24
00:03:29,897 --> 00:03:30,898
Barley.

25
00:03:34,736 --> 00:03:35,903
Rice!

26
00:03:37,655 --> 00:03:39,699
Barley.

27
00:03:42,118 --> 00:03:42,952
Wanna die?

28
00:03:43,036 --> 00:03:44,746
Don't do this.

29
00:03:45,413 --> 00:03:47,206
If you do, everyone will die.

30
00:03:57,091 --> 00:03:57,925
Barley.

31
00:04:00,428 --> 00:04:02,638
No matter how many times you try,
I'll stop you.

32
00:04:06,934 --> 00:04:09,520
How dare you get in the shepherd's way!

33
00:04:10,855 --> 00:04:13,608
If you're defective,
act like one and stay out of my way!

34
00:04:17,987 --> 00:04:20,198
You're a nobody,
yet you're trying to be a hero?

35
00:04:45,056 --> 00:04:46,349
Sure,

36
00:04:47,809 --> 00:04:49,685
people may call me Sappy Sap,

37
00:04:50,186 --> 00:04:53,564
and yeah, most people would agree
that I'm a nobody,

38
00:04:54,941 --> 00:04:57,819
but I won't sit back and let people die.

39
00:05:02,156 --> 00:05:03,408
Sorry.

40
00:05:05,201 --> 00:05:06,577
This is going to hurt.

41
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:24,137
What's going on?

42
00:05:25,346 --> 00:05:28,182
Who are those punks,
and why are they causing such a ruckus?

43
00:05:29,016 --> 00:05:30,726
We'll deal with them.

44
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,520
And the surgery?

45
00:05:34,230 --> 00:05:39,068
You lost the child with the eternal heart
from right under your nose!

46
00:05:40,069 --> 00:05:42,071
Finding her again won't be difficult.

47
00:06:06,304 --> 00:06:07,388
Help me.

48
00:06:11,726 --> 00:06:12,643
Help me.

49
00:06:36,042 --> 00:06:36,918
Don't!

50
00:06:45,426 --> 00:06:47,595
Help me!

51
00:06:47,678 --> 00:06:49,639
Please help us!

52
00:06:50,139 --> 00:06:52,725
Please save our brother!

53
00:06:53,434 --> 00:06:54,810
Please!

54
00:06:56,729 --> 00:06:57,730
Do you remember?

55
00:07:00,149 --> 00:07:01,817
How horrible it was?

56
00:07:03,819 --> 00:07:05,071
This is all your fault.

57
00:07:10,451 --> 00:07:13,496
You ruined everything.

58
00:07:13,579 --> 00:07:14,413
See it now?

59
00:07:25,508 --> 00:07:26,342
Stop.

60
00:07:27,552 --> 00:07:30,096
So what if we were experimented on
and it hurt?

61
00:07:30,179 --> 00:07:31,806
Nothing in life is free.

62
00:07:31,889 --> 00:07:34,058
You need to endure some pain to be loved!

63
00:07:36,227 --> 00:07:38,187
Even our birth parents abandoned us.

64
00:07:38,271 --> 00:07:42,108
Father was the only one
who ever called us family!

65
00:07:42,942 --> 00:07:44,151
It's all because of you!

66
00:07:44,777 --> 00:07:46,404
It's all your fault

67
00:07:46,487 --> 00:07:48,489
that we ended up like this!

68
00:07:48,573 --> 00:07:49,949
Stop it!

69
00:08:01,961 --> 00:08:03,504
Goddamn it,

70
00:08:03,588 --> 00:08:06,757
this is so unbearably fun!

71
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:11,554
I'm having a goddamn blast!

72
00:08:18,894 --> 00:08:20,771
Chae-ni, are you okay?

73
00:08:20,855 --> 00:08:24,066
What's going on here? What happened?

74
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:26,068
Something's up with Master!

75
00:08:27,236 --> 00:08:31,741
He suddenly ran out of juice,
and it looks like he's totally broken now.

76
00:08:32,491 --> 00:08:33,534
What?

77
00:08:40,082 --> 00:08:43,669
Freaking impeccable timing, if you ask me!

78
00:08:46,088 --> 00:08:50,968
My arm doesn't hurt one bit,
and this isn't tiring at all!

79
00:08:51,469 --> 00:08:54,221
Honestly!

80
00:08:56,182 --> 00:08:59,477
Ro-bin, push me forward!

81
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,978
I can't hear you!

82
00:09:01,062 --> 00:09:02,396
Darn it!

83
00:09:13,532 --> 00:09:17,703
Master! Snap out of it!

84
00:09:21,457 --> 00:09:22,541
Master!

85
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,531
That's enough.

86
00:09:54,407 --> 00:09:55,741
You can stop now.

87
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,126
The truth is…

88
00:10:07,503 --> 00:10:08,838
I wanted to save him.

89
00:10:14,927 --> 00:10:17,054
I wanted to save him, but…

90
00:10:36,741 --> 00:10:37,867
I know.

91
00:10:39,827 --> 00:10:40,953
I get it.

92
00:10:41,954 --> 00:10:43,122
So

93
00:10:43,622 --> 00:10:45,207
please stop now.

94
00:10:46,459 --> 00:10:48,586
We'll all die at this rate.

95
00:11:07,605 --> 00:11:08,564
Master.

96
00:11:08,647 --> 00:11:11,609
Are you okay? Hey, open your eyes!

97
00:11:13,778 --> 00:11:14,737
Just go.

98
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:17,990
What are you talking about?
I came back so we can return together!

99
00:11:18,073 --> 00:11:21,160
I'll just be a burden to you.

100
00:11:23,245 --> 00:11:24,079
Leave me here.

101
00:11:25,915 --> 00:11:26,999
Should we?

102
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,169
Snap out of it, Choi Un-jeong!

103
00:11:32,338 --> 00:11:33,506
It's <i>Lee </i>Un-jeong.

104
00:11:35,883 --> 00:11:36,717
Ro-bin.

105
00:11:37,218 --> 00:11:39,345
You carry Master on your back!

106
00:11:39,845 --> 00:11:41,430
I can't do it.

107
00:11:41,514 --> 00:11:43,224
I have zero strength left.

108
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:46,811
Me too. I don't even have the strength
to insult him.

109
00:11:47,394 --> 00:11:49,271
-I'm beat.
-Damn you two.

110
00:11:50,064 --> 00:11:50,981
Here we go.

111
00:11:57,321 --> 00:11:58,489
Hold onto me, everyone!

112
00:12:03,369 --> 00:12:04,954
Hey, Eun Chae-ni, wait. Wait, I--

113
00:12:18,926 --> 00:12:20,886
What… Where are we? Why are we here?

114
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:23,180
It looks like a chapel.

115
00:12:23,722 --> 00:12:24,932
What do we do?

116
00:12:25,015 --> 00:12:27,476
We must still be
in the Church of Eternal Salvation!

117
00:12:28,185 --> 00:12:29,895
We were meant to go to Master's.

118
00:12:29,979 --> 00:12:32,815
I got distracted at the last minute
because of damn Mr. Son!

119
00:12:38,654 --> 00:12:40,739
I wouldn't even be here
if it wasn't for them!

120
00:12:40,823 --> 00:12:43,534
How could they whiz off
and leave me behind like that?

121
00:12:45,494 --> 00:12:48,664
This is crossing a line
even for you, Lady Trainwreck!

122
00:13:08,893 --> 00:13:10,352
This isn't fun at all.

123
00:13:10,436 --> 00:13:12,521
I'm scared to death.

124
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:16,233
I don't want to die!

125
00:13:17,776 --> 00:13:20,279
I really don't want to die!

126
00:13:20,362 --> 00:13:24,450
I don't even know which lie made me stick.

127
00:13:25,367 --> 00:13:26,827
My arm hurt so much!

128
00:13:26,911 --> 00:13:30,539
It was so tiring! Exhausting!

129
00:13:33,584 --> 00:13:37,129
I had enough strength left
to carry Mr. Oddball on my back

130
00:13:37,212 --> 00:13:40,132
and run away.

131
00:14:06,241 --> 00:14:08,577
Chae-ni, what do we do now?

132
00:14:10,287 --> 00:14:14,249
The minute Master wakes up,
you get him out of here!

133
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:18,545
And even if you do get out,
don't tell Grandma anything.

134
00:14:18,629 --> 00:14:20,089
She'll be so worried.

135
00:14:20,172 --> 00:14:21,632
She already knows.

136
00:14:23,008 --> 00:14:23,884
What?

137
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:26,345
How?

138
00:14:26,428 --> 00:14:27,805
Why would you tell her?

139
00:14:27,888 --> 00:14:30,224
I didn't need to tell her
because she already knew.

140
00:14:30,307 --> 00:14:31,934
Your grandma knows everything!

141
00:14:32,017 --> 00:14:33,727
She even helped us with this plan!

142
00:14:36,605 --> 00:14:38,357
This is unbelievable.

143
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:43,445
Well, anyway, you do whatever it takes
to get out of here! Don't get soft!

144
00:14:44,363 --> 00:14:46,865
I'll go back and find Royal Nightmare--

145
00:14:49,118 --> 00:14:50,536
Eun Chae-ni!

146
00:14:52,579 --> 00:14:53,622
Eun Chae-ni!

147
00:15:30,117 --> 00:15:31,368
What is that?

148
00:15:39,168 --> 00:15:41,837
Serum we obtained from that child.

149
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:44,089
It won't be as potent
as the heart of eternity,

150
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:48,302
but it should work as a booster
for cell regeneration.

151
00:15:48,385 --> 00:15:52,264
Just keeping your lungs from hardening
should make breathing easier.

152
00:15:52,973 --> 00:15:53,849
If

153
00:15:55,392 --> 00:15:57,978
something happens to me,

154
00:15:58,937 --> 00:16:02,316
kill them all as I previously ordered.

155
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:03,484
Yes, sir!

156
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:09,907
If you're confident,

157
00:16:10,657 --> 00:16:12,326
go ahead!

158
00:17:17,683 --> 00:17:18,517
Dr. Ha?

159
00:18:08,567 --> 00:18:09,443
What

160
00:18:10,903 --> 00:18:11,987
happened to me?

161
00:18:47,105 --> 00:18:48,857
Father, 3972 is--

162
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:53,946
How are you feeling right now?

163
00:19:01,411 --> 00:19:02,913
I feel strong.

164
00:19:04,998 --> 00:19:06,625
And the pain is gone.

165
00:19:07,251 --> 00:19:08,794
It's even easier to breathe.

166
00:19:09,795 --> 00:19:11,380
All my movements

167
00:19:12,172 --> 00:19:13,674
feel sharp.

168
00:19:25,686 --> 00:19:27,229
Dr. Ha Won-do.

169
00:19:28,438 --> 00:19:29,481
You

170
00:19:30,315 --> 00:19:32,109
really did it.

171
00:19:35,153 --> 00:19:37,239
I can't believe this is possible.

172
00:19:41,868 --> 00:19:42,953
This is the moment

173
00:19:43,453 --> 00:19:46,748
I make history!

174
00:19:55,465 --> 00:19:56,633
Dr. Ha?

175
00:19:58,343 --> 00:20:00,137
The graph is spiking.

176
00:20:10,022 --> 00:20:13,692
What's wrong with my heart?
It's beating too fast.

177
00:20:15,277 --> 00:20:17,404
Bring me some amiodarone. Now!

178
00:20:26,621 --> 00:20:28,415
Mr. Nam, are you okay?

179
00:20:34,046 --> 00:20:35,464
Why is this happening?

180
00:20:36,089 --> 00:20:38,383
Has it already worn off?

181
00:20:41,678 --> 00:20:42,846
The serum.

182
00:20:42,929 --> 00:20:44,931
Bring me more of that drug you injected.

183
00:20:45,432 --> 00:20:47,976
That was all of the first batch
of serum we produced.

184
00:20:48,852 --> 00:20:52,356
Don't just stand there and gawk!
Do something!

185
00:20:58,612 --> 00:20:59,988
Ha Won-do.

186
00:21:00,864 --> 00:21:02,574
Did you do this on purpose?

187
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:08,038
No.

188
00:21:08,789 --> 00:21:09,623
I

189
00:21:10,415 --> 00:21:12,709
deserve to live longer!

190
00:21:13,794 --> 00:21:16,463
I can't go out like this!

191
00:21:17,214 --> 00:21:20,175
I am the great Nam Sun-gyu!

192
00:21:20,675 --> 00:21:23,178
I achieved so much!

193
00:21:24,137 --> 00:21:25,722
Me!

194
00:21:26,306 --> 00:21:28,183
I, Nam Sun-gyu…

195
00:21:44,783 --> 00:21:45,992
What the…

196
00:21:56,044 --> 00:21:56,878
Don't move!

197
00:21:57,629 --> 00:21:58,839
Stop right there.

198
00:22:06,805 --> 00:22:10,642
You will not attack anyone in this room.

199
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:13,562
And forget everything
that happened in here.

200
00:22:18,358 --> 00:22:20,152
Await your next orders outside.

201
00:22:20,735 --> 00:22:22,028
Everyone, outside.

202
00:22:29,744 --> 00:22:30,745
Father.

203
00:22:31,955 --> 00:22:32,956
Are you all right?

204
00:22:34,666 --> 00:22:37,002
Was the dosage the problem?

205
00:22:37,669 --> 00:22:40,839
The guinea pig's numbers were all fine.

206
00:22:41,590 --> 00:22:43,091
Or was it due to

207
00:22:43,592 --> 00:22:45,510
individual differences after all?

208
00:22:46,344 --> 00:22:48,346
What will you do
about Chairman Nam Sun-gyu?

209
00:22:49,639 --> 00:22:52,767
Though it was fleeting,
he got to experience youth again.

210
00:22:52,851 --> 00:22:54,895
He should be satisfied with that.

211
00:22:56,980 --> 00:23:00,317
In any case,
it was a meaningful experiment.

212
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,611
I see hope on the horizon.

213
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:07,282
Does that mean you can fix us now, Father?

214
00:23:08,617 --> 00:23:11,536
There are still questions
that need answering.

215
00:23:12,245 --> 00:23:15,665
To do that,
we need more of that child's blood.

216
00:23:18,043 --> 00:23:19,586
That crazy son of a…

217
00:23:29,262 --> 00:23:30,931
Wait, hold up!

218
00:23:43,568 --> 00:23:44,903
Ouch.

219
00:23:46,029 --> 00:23:47,072
Man, that hurts.

220
00:23:47,155 --> 00:23:49,908
That was freaky.
Could have gone totally south…

221
00:24:10,178 --> 00:24:11,263
I'm sorry, Father.

222
00:24:12,430 --> 00:24:13,390
Go catch her.

223
00:24:14,683 --> 00:24:18,270
The side effects have spread
to his shoulder, so he shouldn't push it.

224
00:24:18,353 --> 00:24:20,272
In life,

225
00:24:21,106 --> 00:24:26,069
there are times when the rest of your days
boil down to a single moment's decision.

226
00:24:29,281 --> 00:24:30,991
Now is such a time, Ju-ran.

227
00:24:32,784 --> 00:24:37,122
Will you die with your pain,
or will you fight to end it?

228
00:24:39,958 --> 00:24:40,959
You decide.

229
00:25:17,621 --> 00:25:18,955
Stay here. I'll do it.

230
00:25:20,498 --> 00:25:22,792
You're not my guardian. Stop interfering.

231
00:25:24,544 --> 00:25:27,422
And stop trying to stick up for me
in front of Father!

232
00:25:29,215 --> 00:25:31,217
It makes me look weaker than you.

233
00:25:31,301 --> 00:25:34,721
What if the side effects spread
and harden your heart?

234
00:25:35,722 --> 00:25:38,183
-Are you just going to die?
-Stay out of it!

235
00:25:39,017 --> 00:25:40,393
Listen to me!

236
00:25:41,686 --> 00:25:43,813
What, will you use your ability on me too?

237
00:25:44,814 --> 00:25:46,608
It wouldn't work anyway.

238
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:53,323
Father gave me this.

239
00:25:53,823 --> 00:25:56,951
He made it specifically
to block out your ability.

240
00:25:59,663 --> 00:26:00,580
Father?

241
00:26:07,671 --> 00:26:08,797
<i>Why would he…</i>

242
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:11,883
You always want to peer into
other people's thoughts.

243
00:26:11,966 --> 00:26:14,969
Even I know that.
Did you really think Father wouldn't?

244
00:26:16,054 --> 00:26:18,014
I just wanted to protect our family.

245
00:26:18,098 --> 00:26:19,599
Don't you mean control us?

246
00:26:25,605 --> 00:26:27,148
I don't want to die like this.

247
00:26:27,816 --> 00:26:29,234
So, Ju-ran…

248
00:26:31,236 --> 00:26:32,904
let's each do our part.

249
00:26:34,531 --> 00:26:35,740
Don't be suspicious.

250
00:26:35,824 --> 00:26:37,617
To protect our family,

251
00:26:38,618 --> 00:26:39,869
we need to trust Father.

252
00:27:25,206 --> 00:27:26,374
Fuck.

253
00:27:30,170 --> 00:27:31,296
I'm so pissed.

254
00:27:40,764 --> 00:27:43,516
What, never seen a person
drop from the sky before?

255
00:27:44,434 --> 00:27:46,269
What are you all staring at?

256
00:27:46,853 --> 00:27:48,938
How rude!

257
00:27:54,277 --> 00:27:55,612
Come here. Hurry.

258
00:27:55,695 --> 00:27:56,946
Why are you still…

259
00:28:02,035 --> 00:28:03,161
Be saved.

260
00:28:04,537 --> 00:28:06,289
Have a nice time.

261
00:28:08,082 --> 00:28:09,501
Gain eternal life.

262
00:28:10,001 --> 00:28:11,127
Eternal life.

263
00:28:12,962 --> 00:28:14,589
-Is that Trainwreck?
-Hearty House?

264
00:28:14,672 --> 00:28:18,343
-Why's that brat here?
-Why's the Trainwreck of Haeseong here?

265
00:28:18,426 --> 00:28:21,346
Bet she came here because she's scared
of the apocalypse too.

266
00:28:21,429 --> 00:28:24,098
What kind of ruckus
is she planning to cause here?

267
00:28:24,182 --> 00:28:25,767
She should stay out of trouble.

268
00:28:25,850 --> 00:28:27,936
Only natural to want to live.

269
00:28:33,525 --> 00:28:35,652
You must have cashed out a lot
as offerings.

270
00:28:38,112 --> 00:28:41,241
Where did you get the matching fits?

271
00:28:41,324 --> 00:28:43,409
Have you all got money to burn?

272
00:28:45,578 --> 00:28:47,121
But how unfortunate.

273
00:28:47,831 --> 00:28:51,793
Listen up, everyone.
There is no apocalypse.

274
00:28:53,211 --> 00:28:56,047
Even if you're sick of life,
you have to keep living.

275
00:28:56,130 --> 00:28:57,590
Don't give them your money!

276
00:28:59,676 --> 00:29:02,971
What will you all do
if the apocalypse <i>doesn't </i>come?

277
00:29:03,471 --> 00:29:04,347
By the way,

278
00:29:05,723 --> 00:29:09,310
do you all know that they're conducting
evil experiments down there?

279
00:29:10,687 --> 00:29:12,480
Don't regret it later,

280
00:29:12,981 --> 00:29:16,484
and please, just snap out of it
and go home now!

281
00:29:18,361 --> 00:29:19,404
You there.

282
00:29:19,487 --> 00:29:21,406
Mr. Heo, from the general store.

283
00:29:21,906 --> 00:29:24,784
And behind you,
even the <i>hotteok </i>lady is here.

284
00:29:24,868 --> 00:29:28,037
Why don't you go and sell
your <i>hotteok </i>instead?

285
00:29:28,621 --> 00:29:31,457
I said go home already!

286
00:29:47,515 --> 00:29:49,267
-What the…
<i>-Can you hear me, believers?</i>

287
00:29:51,185 --> 00:29:53,730
<i>Outsiders who want to</i>
<i>bring down our church</i>

288
00:29:53,813 --> 00:29:55,523
<i>have infiltrated the building.</i>

289
00:29:56,608 --> 00:29:58,902
The moment you find them,

290
00:29:59,402 --> 00:30:01,738
capture them and bring them
to the shepherd.

291
00:30:03,531 --> 00:30:05,700
You will be rewarded with grace.

292
00:30:12,123 --> 00:30:14,667
Begone, Church of Eternal Salvation!

293
00:30:14,751 --> 00:30:16,669
Begone!

294
00:30:17,503 --> 00:30:19,923
Return our children to us!

295
00:30:20,006 --> 00:30:22,258
Return them to us!

296
00:30:22,342 --> 00:30:24,886
Begone, Church of Eternal Salvation!

297
00:30:24,969 --> 00:30:27,305
Begone!

298
00:30:39,025 --> 00:30:41,235
I'm just passing through.

299
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,030
May you receive eternal life.

300
00:30:44,989 --> 00:30:46,074
Why are you…

301
00:30:46,157 --> 00:30:48,201
Why are you doing this all of a sudden?

302
00:30:48,284 --> 00:30:49,160
Stay back, okay?

303
00:30:49,744 --> 00:30:51,913
Move while I'm still asking nicely.

304
00:30:51,996 --> 00:30:54,082
Or else I'll spit on you! Okay?

305
00:30:54,666 --> 00:30:56,709
I'm serious.

306
00:30:56,793 --> 00:30:57,961
I'll spit on you!

307
00:30:59,045 --> 00:30:59,879
What's with you?

308
00:31:00,463 --> 00:31:02,882
Stay back! Don't!
I don't make empty threats!

309
00:31:04,092 --> 00:31:05,551
Believers,

310
00:31:05,635 --> 00:31:09,347
let us all receive the reward of grace!

311
00:31:10,473 --> 00:31:11,391
Stay back!

312
00:31:12,684 --> 00:31:13,977
I told you to stay back.

313
00:31:14,060 --> 00:31:16,813
I said stay back! What are you doing?
You're freaking me out!

314
00:31:16,896 --> 00:31:18,231
Get a hold of yourselves!

315
00:31:18,898 --> 00:31:19,732
Ro-bin!

316
00:31:19,816 --> 00:31:21,859
Hurry. Take Master and run!

317
00:31:23,027 --> 00:31:24,320
I said run, you idiot!

318
00:31:49,137 --> 00:31:50,304
Master!

319
00:32:00,815 --> 00:32:01,774
Here's what we'll do.

320
00:32:02,275 --> 00:32:04,610
First, take Mr. Kang Ro-bin outside.

321
00:32:05,111 --> 00:32:08,281
When you come back, I'll hurl you outside.

322
00:32:09,323 --> 00:32:10,867
That's our only option.

323
00:32:10,950 --> 00:32:12,452
I'll find Mr. Son Gyeong-hun.

324
00:32:13,119 --> 00:32:13,953
I don't want to.

325
00:32:15,371 --> 00:32:16,289
Don't be stubborn.

326
00:32:16,372 --> 00:32:17,457
I said I don't want to.

327
00:32:20,001 --> 00:32:21,169
Let me save you.

328
00:32:22,128 --> 00:32:23,337
That's why I'm here.

329
00:32:25,006 --> 00:32:28,718
I won't let you be the only one
who looks cool. It makes me jealous.

330
00:32:29,635 --> 00:32:32,847
I'm the type
who'd prefer to save than be saved.

331
00:32:33,598 --> 00:32:34,599
Hey, Master!

332
00:32:35,433 --> 00:32:37,852
I think we should get out of here
as soon as possible.

333
00:33:24,524 --> 00:33:29,195
EPISODE 7
THE GUARDIANS OF HAESEONG CITY PART 1

334
00:33:30,154 --> 00:33:32,490
Give us back our families!

335
00:33:32,573 --> 00:33:34,492
Give them back!

336
00:33:35,493 --> 00:33:37,286
Yes, how did it go?

337
00:33:37,787 --> 00:33:39,664
Did you talk to the police chief?

338
00:33:39,747 --> 00:33:41,207
A total waste of breath.

339
00:33:41,707 --> 00:33:45,878
Looks like the church
buttered up the police chief too.

340
00:33:45,962 --> 00:33:48,214
If that's the case,
the police are useless too.

341
00:33:49,507 --> 00:33:51,425
What about on your end? Nothing yet?

342
00:33:51,509 --> 00:33:52,885
Give them back!

343
00:33:53,386 --> 00:33:54,846
There seems to be a delay.

344
00:33:54,929 --> 00:33:58,391
Even the followers who were outside
just went back in all of a sudden.

345
00:33:59,183 --> 00:34:01,894
<i>I have a bad feeling about this.</i>
<i>What should we do?</i>

346
00:34:03,729 --> 00:34:05,439
Your turn, babe!

347
00:34:05,523 --> 00:34:06,357
Do it!

348
00:34:08,276 --> 00:34:09,694
Do it. Go again.

349
00:34:09,777 --> 00:34:10,820
One more try.

350
00:34:12,530 --> 00:34:15,491
-Nice one!
-I hit it!

351
00:34:15,575 --> 00:34:17,994
Can we have this one here?

352
00:34:18,494 --> 00:34:20,955
Thank you. Have a nice evening.

353
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:23,416
Jun-mo.

354
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,501
We'd better go with Plan B.

355
00:34:26,002 --> 00:34:27,086
Get ready.

356
00:34:30,798 --> 00:34:32,133
Begone!

357
00:34:32,216 --> 00:34:34,594
Begone!

358
00:34:34,677 --> 00:34:36,929
Give us back our children!

359
00:34:37,013 --> 00:34:38,431
Okay, we're going with Plan B.

360
00:35:02,872 --> 00:35:04,624
You dare hang up on me?

361
00:35:08,252 --> 00:35:10,171
Is this for the parade tomorrow?

362
00:35:10,254 --> 00:35:12,840
It looks so good on you, Cheong!

363
00:35:15,009 --> 00:35:15,968
What about Dad?

364
00:35:16,469 --> 00:35:17,678
Is he still not home?

365
00:35:18,971 --> 00:35:21,891
Leave him be.
He's probably rolling around somewhere.

366
00:35:46,582 --> 00:35:49,585
Check the number of gas tanks here.
And move fast.

367
00:35:49,669 --> 00:35:50,670
Yes, will do.

368
00:35:50,753 --> 00:35:52,463
Move all the chemicals we can save.

369
00:36:06,602 --> 00:36:09,981
I'm not scared at all. Zero fear. Zilch.

370
00:36:10,481 --> 00:36:12,149
This is a piece of cake.

371
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:14,235
It's honestly laughable.

372
00:36:15,569 --> 00:36:17,238
I'm terrified.

373
00:36:17,905 --> 00:36:19,532
I'm Song Dae-kwan.

374
00:36:20,408 --> 00:36:22,994
This is the hardest thing ever.
I'm tearing up.

375
00:36:23,494 --> 00:36:25,121
I'm Tae Jin-ah.

376
00:36:26,497 --> 00:36:27,707
I'm Son Gyeong-hun.

377
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:29,792
I'm President Kim Dae-jung.

378
00:36:36,966 --> 00:36:38,801
I'm Lee Deok-hwa.

379
00:36:39,427 --> 00:36:40,469
I'm Son Gyeong-hun--

380
00:36:46,809 --> 00:36:48,978
-Hey, grab it.
-Yes, I'll grab this side.

381
00:36:49,061 --> 00:36:51,230
Okay, grab it properly. Now lift.

382
00:36:52,606 --> 00:36:55,526
Three, two, one.

383
00:37:16,088 --> 00:37:17,548
-Two, one.
-Two, one.

384
00:37:28,559 --> 00:37:31,520
Are we going ahead
with the apocalypse plan?

385
00:37:35,524 --> 00:37:38,069
The prophecy will be fulfilled as planned.

386
00:37:39,236 --> 00:37:41,030
Because that's where salvation begins.

387
00:37:44,283 --> 00:37:47,787
Is dousing the people of Haeseong
with a chemical…

388
00:37:49,872 --> 00:37:51,040
really salvation?

389
00:37:52,792 --> 00:37:53,834
What do you mean?

390
00:37:57,254 --> 00:38:02,426
I believed Dad would save us,
but I'm not so sure anymore.

391
00:38:05,930 --> 00:38:07,181
Can't we just

392
00:38:07,973 --> 00:38:09,683
leave this place?

393
00:38:10,684 --> 00:38:13,229
We can't betray Father.

394
00:38:14,063 --> 00:38:16,607
We will never leave.

395
00:38:17,650 --> 00:38:18,692
Why not?

396
00:38:19,902 --> 00:38:20,736
Why?

397
00:38:27,993 --> 00:38:29,745
This is why.

398
00:38:30,913 --> 00:38:33,541
Because Father is the only one
who will protect us.

399
00:38:39,296 --> 00:38:41,048
Leave before it's too late.

400
00:38:41,132 --> 00:38:42,716
And be careful not to get hurt.

401
00:38:44,885 --> 00:38:46,137
You still think I'm a kid.

402
00:38:49,014 --> 00:38:50,433
Look after Pal-ho.

403
00:38:52,518 --> 00:38:53,561
Let's go.

404
00:38:54,353 --> 00:38:55,229
Open it.

405
00:39:02,736 --> 00:39:03,904
The apocalypse?

406
00:39:06,574 --> 00:39:07,783
That's great.

407
00:39:08,284 --> 00:39:09,660
The apocalypse.

408
00:39:10,995 --> 00:39:15,458
If they douse Haeseong with that chemical,
what will become of my dear Moon Mi-hui?

409
00:39:17,501 --> 00:39:19,670
What about my darling Cheong?

410
00:39:31,974 --> 00:39:33,309
That'll be fun.

411
00:39:33,809 --> 00:39:36,312
A family of defectives.

412
00:39:45,196 --> 00:39:46,572
It'll be so

413
00:39:47,156 --> 00:39:48,199
goddamn

414
00:39:48,699 --> 00:39:50,743
ridiculously fun!

415
00:40:11,472 --> 00:40:12,932
Ro-bin!

416
00:40:20,105 --> 00:40:21,232
Go.

417
00:40:23,734 --> 00:40:24,818
Go.

418
00:40:26,195 --> 00:40:27,404
Go!

419
00:40:39,166 --> 00:40:40,292
I'm safe.

420
00:40:41,168 --> 00:40:42,711
Thank you, Master.

421
00:40:46,340 --> 00:40:48,884
Great. You did well, Kang Ro-bin.

422
00:40:49,593 --> 00:40:53,264
For a guy this out of shape who once
landed in the ER after a 100-meter run,

423
00:40:53,764 --> 00:40:55,307
you did a pretty good job.

424
00:40:55,391 --> 00:40:56,433
Kudos.

425
00:41:06,610 --> 00:41:08,946
So you somehow managed to get this far.

426
00:41:09,446 --> 00:41:11,365
Now stop playing hide-and-seek

427
00:41:12,575 --> 00:41:13,492
and hand her over.

428
00:41:14,868 --> 00:41:15,703
Ms. Eun Chae-ni.

429
00:41:16,203 --> 00:41:18,080
Take Mr. Kang Ro-bin and go.

430
00:41:19,123 --> 00:41:22,334
But, Master, I'm going to end up
back here anyway.

431
00:41:22,418 --> 00:41:23,502
Exactly.

432
00:41:24,461 --> 00:41:26,297
First, get Mr. Kang Ro-bin out of here,

433
00:41:27,756 --> 00:41:29,008
then come back

434
00:41:29,758 --> 00:41:30,718
and help me.

435
00:41:34,096 --> 00:41:35,306
Hang in there

436
00:41:36,015 --> 00:41:37,308
until I get back.

437
00:41:45,983 --> 00:41:47,693
I've clocked her pattern.

438
00:41:47,776 --> 00:41:50,195
Even if she gets away,
she'll end up back here.

439
00:41:51,405 --> 00:41:52,948
Like a broken blinker.

440
00:41:55,367 --> 00:41:56,410
Which is why I intend…

441
00:41:59,246 --> 00:42:00,664
to end this before she returns.

442
00:42:10,424 --> 00:42:12,343
Ro-bin, I managed to make it
to your place.

443
00:42:14,053 --> 00:42:14,887
A weapon.

444
00:42:16,388 --> 00:42:17,348
A weapon.

445
00:42:21,685 --> 00:42:23,187
Would these help?

446
00:42:49,463 --> 00:42:50,422
A weapon.

447
00:42:50,506 --> 00:42:52,591
A weapon!

448
00:42:52,675 --> 00:42:54,551
Have anything that I can use as a weapon?

449
00:42:54,635 --> 00:42:57,012
A weapon.
Anything that can be used as a weapon.

450
00:42:57,096 --> 00:42:58,639
Anything that might help.

451
00:44:01,994 --> 00:44:03,829
HARDWARE, BUILDING MATERIALS

452
00:44:05,205 --> 00:44:06,582
That's more like it.

453
00:44:25,851 --> 00:44:27,644
Why are you going this far?

454
00:44:29,313 --> 00:44:31,064
You're dying too.

455
00:44:32,232 --> 00:44:35,861
Don't you know that we can all live
if we offer that child up?

456
00:44:38,947 --> 00:44:41,742
A life that you can only live
by killing someone.

457
00:44:43,118 --> 00:44:44,203
A bit low, isn't it?

458
00:44:49,416 --> 00:44:51,502
It's not like you don't know

459
00:44:52,085 --> 00:44:53,420
why we ended up like this.

460
00:44:55,881 --> 00:44:57,341
Doesn't it piss you off?

461
00:44:59,259 --> 00:45:01,345
You're doing exactly what they did to us.

462
00:45:01,428 --> 00:45:03,222
Stop acting all high and mighty.

463
00:45:04,181 --> 00:45:07,810
You offered that child up
to find your mom.

464
00:45:09,937 --> 00:45:11,605
It didn't really matter to me…

465
00:45:14,149 --> 00:45:15,984
whatever Ha Won-do was doing again…

466
00:45:18,487 --> 00:45:19,696
or what happened to that child.

467
00:45:23,408 --> 00:45:26,245
Then stay out of this
and piss off, you bastard.

468
00:45:28,705 --> 00:45:29,665
I should.

469
00:45:32,501 --> 00:45:34,169
I'd like to…

470
00:45:36,755 --> 00:45:37,798
but I can't.

471
00:45:39,508 --> 00:45:40,384
Why not?

472
00:45:42,511 --> 00:45:44,847
Did you get attached to those losers?

473
00:45:47,599 --> 00:45:48,767
I wonder.

474
00:45:51,770 --> 00:45:52,813
Did I?

475
00:45:52,896 --> 00:45:55,607
You fucking idiot.

476
00:45:57,901 --> 00:45:59,069
So…

477
00:46:01,446 --> 00:46:02,948
kill me right here.

478
00:46:04,408 --> 00:46:06,034
Or you'll be the one to die.

479
00:48:22,379 --> 00:48:24,297
Move aside!

480
00:48:31,054 --> 00:48:32,347
Get back!

481
00:48:59,541 --> 00:49:01,543
Lady Trainwreck!

482
00:49:02,377 --> 00:49:05,130
-Lady Trainwreck. You came to save--
-Move aside!

483
00:49:05,213 --> 00:49:08,091
Move aside, damn it.
Don't come any closer, okay?

484
00:49:08,175 --> 00:49:09,634
Go! Run away!

485
00:49:09,718 --> 00:49:10,594
Get lost!

486
00:49:11,678 --> 00:49:13,096
Block the door for now!

487
00:49:13,180 --> 00:49:15,557
Why?

488
00:49:15,640 --> 00:49:17,559
Why?

489
00:49:18,894 --> 00:49:20,020
Move out of the way!

490
00:49:25,442 --> 00:49:26,651
What are you doing?

491
00:49:26,735 --> 00:49:27,944
Get over here!

492
00:49:28,737 --> 00:49:30,238
Hurry!

493
00:49:39,164 --> 00:49:39,998
You bastard, you--

494
00:49:40,082 --> 00:49:41,625
Perfect timing!

495
00:49:49,091 --> 00:49:51,510
Master! I'm here!

496
00:50:01,394 --> 00:50:02,479
Master?

497
00:50:13,073 --> 00:50:14,282
Master.

498
00:50:17,119 --> 00:50:17,953
Let's go.

499
00:50:18,036 --> 00:50:19,663
We have to get out of here.

500
00:50:19,746 --> 00:50:20,956
We find Master first.

501
00:50:21,039 --> 00:50:22,290
Are you crazy? No!

502
00:50:23,250 --> 00:50:24,251
I'm out!

503
00:50:25,001 --> 00:50:28,213
I came to save your life,
yet you're going to run away by yourself?

504
00:50:28,296 --> 00:50:29,881
Hey, let's get the facts straight.

505
00:50:29,965 --> 00:50:31,591
I came in here to save you,

506
00:50:31,675 --> 00:50:35,095
and you ditched me and ran away
with Ro-bin and Oddball!

507
00:50:35,178 --> 00:50:38,223
So I came back, didn't I?
You should be grateful I saved you!

508
00:50:38,306 --> 00:50:42,769
Which is why I'm going to get out of here
while I'm still alive. Now, right now!

509
00:50:43,270 --> 00:50:45,105
But Master is alone right now!

510
00:50:45,188 --> 00:50:47,941
The apocalypse is nigh for Haeseong!

511
00:50:48,733 --> 00:50:50,360
A real apocalypse!

512
00:50:56,658 --> 00:50:58,285
Mr. Son, no way.

513
00:50:59,536 --> 00:51:01,037
Have you become a believer?

514
00:51:02,330 --> 00:51:03,206
Since when?

515
00:51:03,290 --> 00:51:04,916
How did that happen?

516
00:51:05,500 --> 00:51:07,544
I heard it with my own ears.

517
00:51:08,044 --> 00:51:11,673
Those people, those crazy people,
said they're going to destroy Haeseong.

518
00:51:12,674 --> 00:51:14,009
That chemical,

519
00:51:14,092 --> 00:51:15,177
that phenol!

520
00:51:15,677 --> 00:51:17,679
They're going to spray it
all over Haeseong.

521
00:51:17,762 --> 00:51:20,223
On every single person in Haeseong!

522
00:51:21,016 --> 00:51:25,187
Everyone, including my dear Moon Mi-hui
and darling Cheong.

523
00:51:55,467 --> 00:51:56,593
Let's go.

524
00:52:10,607 --> 00:52:11,775
Shepherd!

525
00:52:12,609 --> 00:52:13,568
No.

526
00:52:28,500 --> 00:52:29,417
Pal-ho?

527
00:52:31,753 --> 00:52:32,879
Ju-ran.

528
00:52:35,298 --> 00:52:36,299
What do I do?

529
00:52:39,135 --> 00:52:40,262
Father will be…

530
00:52:42,931 --> 00:52:44,599
disappointed in me again.

531
00:53:12,210 --> 00:53:14,379
Kim Pal-ho, our shepherd,

532
00:53:14,921 --> 00:53:16,506
has been martyred.

533
00:53:19,676 --> 00:53:21,511
Shepherd!

534
00:53:22,595 --> 00:53:23,680
Shepherd!

535
00:53:29,602 --> 00:53:31,021
Shepherd!

536
00:53:32,439 --> 00:53:34,232
Shepherd!

537
00:53:44,284 --> 00:53:45,827
What do we do, Eun Chae-ni?

538
00:53:46,328 --> 00:53:48,455
We're all doomed now.

539
00:54:19,402 --> 00:54:23,114
<i>An apocalypse really is coming.</i>

540
00:55:03,863 --> 00:55:07,242
HAESEONG MILLENNIUM FIREWORKS FESTIVAL
DATE: DECEMBER 31, 1999

541
00:58:33,406 --> 00:58:38,411
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

